  - reply to the old digest post with `@LLMeets_bot зарегистрировать`
  - aliases: `register`, `/register`, `зарегистрируй`, `регистрация`
  - the bot extracts `post_url` from `reply_to_message`, parses Loom URL/video ID, meeting title, Google Doc and Transcript Doc links, then writes the publication into the same state DB that AIcallorder uses through the register endpoint flow
  - after registration, `preview`, `создать`, and `обновить` work for that old post
- Explicit commands `обновить`, `коммент`, `чеклист`, and daily-to-weekly require an existing CRM task binding or a task id in the command.
- `обновить` updates only safe task fields:
  - `TITLE`
  - `DESCRIPTION`
  - `TAGS` when present
- `обновить` also appends the source comment to the task, but does not recreate checklists.
- If no target task is known, `обновить` returns an error instead of creating a new task.
- `обновить` is now a merge/update command, not a destructive replacement:
  - reads current CRM task description first
  - if the task has no MeetingDigestBot point structure yet, saves the current CRM description as `Point 1. Предыдущий контекст задачи из CRM`
  - appends the meeting from the tagged/replied post as the next `Point N`
  - if the same source post already exists as a point, replaces only that point
  - uses plain-text markers `=== MEETING_DIGEST_POINT ... ===` for stable re-runs
  - creates/restores a separate checklist group `Point N: <meeting title>` with QA/PM items from that meeting

### Comment behavior update (2026-05-01)

- `коммент` / `comment` now writes meeting results, not just a short sync marker.
- The comment is built from processed AIcallorder artifacts by `loom_video_id`:
  - summary from the processed transcript
  - accepted decisions
  - action items / commitments with owner, due, status when present
  - completed / confirmed items
  - blockers
  - remaining tech debt
  - business requests for estimation
  - open questions
  - source links: Loom, Google Doc, Doc section, Transcript Doc, Transcript section
- The command still requires a target CRM task:
  - reply to a registered digest post: `@LLMeets_bot коммент 168334`
  - or use explicit post link: `@LLMeets_bot https://t.me/c/<chat>/<message> коммент 168334`
- If the digest post is old and was not registered by AIcallorder, first reply to the old post with:
  - `@LLMeets_bot зарегистрировать`
