### CRM comment formatting prompt / rules

Use these rules for any future LLM prompt that prepares text specifically for Bitrix task comments:

```text
Сформируй комментарий для CRM-задачи в plain text.
Не используй markdown-таблицы, HTML-таблицы и строки вида `item | owner=... | due=... | status=...`.
Если в исходных данных есть таблица, преобразуй каждую строку таблицы в отдельный пункт списка.
Формат структурированных пунктов:

- Основной текст пункта
  Ответственный: имя
  Срок: дата или "не указан"
  Статус: статус

Для запросов на оценку:

- Название запроса
  Приоритет: высокий/средний/низкий
  Инициатор: имя, если известно
  Контекст: кратко
  Заметки к оценке: кратко

Не выводи пустые поля и значения "-".
Не используй символ `|` как разделитель колонок.
Заголовки разделов оставляй обычными строками без markdown-разметки.
```

- Runtime formatter also protects comments from bad table rendering:
  - markdown tables are converted into plain text rows
  - pipe metadata like `owner=`, `due=`, `status=`, `priority=` is converted into indented fields

### Bitrix publication actor update (2026-05-01)

- All new MeetingDigestBot tasks must be created in project `GROUP_ID=512` with:
  - `CREATED_BY=114736`
  - `RESPONSIBLE_ID=114736`
  - `AUDITORS=50760,127124,137230,51977`
- All task comments must be published through `task.commentitem.add` with:
  - `AUTHOR_ID=114736`
- Runtime env keys:
  - `BITRIX_ACTOR_USER_ID=114736`
  - `BITRIX_DEFAULT_RESPONSIBLE_ID=114736`
  - `BITRIX_CREATED_BY_ID=114736`
  - `BITRIX_DEFAULT_AUDITOR_IDS=50760,127124,137230,51977`
- Checklist limitation:
  - Portal manifest for `task.checklistitem.add` exposes writable fields only for `PARENT_ID`, `TITLE`, `SORT_INDEX`, `IS_COMPLETE`, `IS_IMPORTANT`, `MEMBERS`.
  - `CREATED_BY` is readable/sortable but not writable, so checklist item author is the REST caller/webhook user.
  - To make checklist items visually authored by user `114736`, the Bitrix webhook/token itself must be issued under user `114736`.

### Daily plan parser update (2026-05-04)

- Added a separate `#daily` plan parser for daily team planning meetings.
- Source meetings are included only when:
  - title contains `#daily`
  - or `meeting_type=daily`
  - or processed artifacts contain `#daily` in tags/hashtags.
- Recommended spoken format:
  - say the full person name as a separate line
  - then say `План на сегодня`, `Блокеры`, optionally `Сделано вчера`
  - then list short actionable points.
- The parser uses `meeting_digest_bot/people_directory.json` to map spoken names and aliases to Bitrix user IDs.
- Daily plan checklist groups are created per person.
- Each checklist item can include Bitrix checklist `MEMBERS`, so the responsible user is attached directly to the item.
- Telegram command:
  - `@LLMeets_bot план 2026-05-04 preview`
  - `@LLMeets_bot план 2026-05-04 создать`
  - `@LLMeets_bot план 2026-05-04 создать команда Bitrix Develop Team`
- CLI command:
  - `python -m meeting_digest_bot sync-daily-plan --report-date 2026-05-04 --action preview`
- API endpoint:
  - `POST /sync/daily-plan`
- Source binding:
  - `source_type=daily_plan`
  - `source_key=<YYYY-MM-DD>:<team_name>`
- Current limitation:
  - parser is intentionally optimized for a structured daily format, not arbitrary conversation.
  - conversational address lines like `Ваня, ты проверял...?` are filtered out to avoid noisy checklist items.

### Daily plan parser v2 update (2026-05-04)

- Implemented `DailyPlanV2Parser`.
- New priority for daily plan extraction:
  - first use structured AIcallorder artifacts: `action_items`, `blockers`, `completed_today`, `summary`;
  - use raw transcript parsing only as fallback when `action_items` are absent;
  - do not create checklist items from raw conversational fragments when structured commitments exist.
- Daily task description now has separate sections:
  - date/team/source meetings;
  - short summary;
  - plan by people;
  - global blockers/dependencies;
  - done/confirmed on daily;
  - manual review only for unassigned structured items.
- Daily task checklists now include only plan commitments from `action_items`.
- Blockers are rendered in the description, not as checklist items.
- Added extra aliases in `people_directory.json`:
  - `Іван`, `Ваня Карповець` -> Иван Карповец / `51977`;
  - `Міша`, `Міша Адам` -> Михаил Конев / `127124`.
- Real production validation:
  - deployed to `/opt/meeting-digest-bot`;
  - services restarted: `meeting-digest-bot-api.service`, `meeting-digest-bot-poller.service`;
  - health check ok;
  - task `168689` was repaired from daily 04.05:
    - old noisy checklist items deleted;
    - description replaced with v2 description;
    - new per-person checklists created with Bitrix members.

